    Title: Young India
    Editor: M. K. Gandhi
    Locus:
      Date: 23 Sept 1926
---
It is easy enough to say, 'I do not believe in God.' For God permits all
things to be said of Him with impunity. He looks at our acts. And any
breach of His Law carries with it, not its vindictive, but its purifying,
compelling, punishment.
